    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nA python dataclass can be passed to `inspect.signature(Cls)` and a signature (I assume of the generated __init__ method) is returned.\r\n\r\nFor a cython cdef dataclass, the `inspect.signature(CyCls)` call raises an exception.\r\n\r\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\r\n\r\ntestdc.pyx:\r\n```cython\r\nimport dataclasses\r\nfrom cython.dataclasses cimport dataclass\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\ncdef class CyDC:\r\n    test: int = 0\r\n\r\n@dataclasses.dataclass\r\nclass PyDC:\r\n    test: int = 0\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\ntest.py:\r\n```\r\nimport inspect\r\nimport pyximport; pyximport.install()\r\n\r\nif __name__ == '__main__':\r\n    import testdc\r\n    print(\">>>> PYTHON dataclass <<<<<\")\r\n    print(inspect.signature(testdc.PyDC))\r\n    print(\">>>> CYTHON dataclass <<<<<\")\r\n    print(inspect.signature(testdc.CyDC))\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nExpected:\r\n```\r\n>>>> PYTHON dataclass <<<<<\r\n(test: 'int' = 0) -> None\r\n>>>> CYTHON dataclass <<<<<\r\n(test: 'int' = 0) -> None\r\n```\r\n\r\nActual:\r\n```\r\n>>>> PYTHON dataclass <<<<<\r\n(test: 'int' = 0) -> None\r\n>>>> CYTHON dataclass <<<<<\r\nTraceback (most recent call last):\r\n...\r\nValueError: no signature found for builtin type <class 'testdc.CyDC'>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### OS\r\n\r\nmacOs\r\n\r\n### Python version\r\n\r\n3.10.4\r\n\r\n### Cython version\r\n\r\n3.0.2\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This is pretty ugly, but as a workaround, I came up with the following:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\nclass _SignatureWrapper:\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.__signature__ = None\r\n\r\n    def _set_from_dataclass(self, cls):\r\n        fields = [(f.name, f.type, f) for f in dataclasses.fields(cls)]\r\n        inst = dataclasses.make_dataclass(cls.__name__, fields)\r\n        self.__signature__ = inspect.signature(inst)\r\n\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\ncdef class CyDC:\r\n    __wrapped__ = _SignatureWrapper()\r\n    test: int = 0\r\n\r\nCyDC.__wrapped__._set_from_dataclass(CyDC)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich allows `inspect.signature(CyDC)` to return something that looks about right",
