            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That suggests we've been a little too successful at disguising Cython dataclasses as dataclasses!\r\n\r\nIt's possibly a little fiddly because we have two methods that can do class initialization (`__cinit__` and `__init__`) so need to get information from two places. But I doubt it's impossible to generate a signature.",
